item.description:
Genre: Pop
Style: Indie Pop, Ballad
Year: 2017
Video Source: Apple Music, thanks Brungor
Audio Source: Qobuz & Apple Music, thanks moi & DanceDanceDance

"Idontwannabeyouanymore" is a song by American singer Billie Eilish from her debut EP, Don't Smile at Me (2017). Eilish and her brother, Finneas O'Connell, co-wrote the song, with the latter solely handling the production. It was released through Darkroom and Interscope Records on July 21, 2017, as the fifth single from the EP. "Idontwannabeyouanymore" finds Eilish singing about self-doubt and negative self-esteem. Musically, the song is pop and R&B track with a jazz and neo soul-influenced melody, that was heavily inspired by Eilish being depressed.

Commercially, "Idontwannabeyouanymore" reached number 96 on the Billboard Hot 100. It has also received several certifications, including double-platinum awards from the Mexican Association of Producers of Phonograms and Videograms, A.C. (AMPROFON) and the Recording Industry Association of America (RIAA).

In December 2017, Eilish premiered a Spotify-released vertical video to accompany the song. It was eventually released on YouTube on January 4, 2018. In the minimalistic visual, it portrays a silver-haired Eilish in an all-white room talking to her reflection in a mirror about how she hates herself. Shweta Patokar writing for Republic World commented that what makes the video scary is how "close it is to reality".

Release Info
The video track is upscaled to 4K with Topaz Video AI and encoded to HEVC 10-bit.
The PCM track is lossless (Qobuz HiRes 24-bit) and synced with Adobe Audition.
The Dolby Atmos track is lossy (E-AC3), synced to the video track by muxing.
The timed lyrics are synced & edited. Enable the subtitles to see the lyrics.
